com.unvired.ump.agent

Interface IProcessAgent


  • public interface IProcessAgent
    The IProcessAgent interface defines the contract between the Unvired infrastructure and the process agent.

    ISVs building custom applications using the Unvired infrastructure need to implement this interface to build server side components. The IBusinessProcess handle allows the process agent to retrieve input from the client and set the result for the client. This handle can also be used to retrieve other contextual information and access useful Unvired internal services when implementing the server side business logic.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void execute()
      The Unvired infrastructure invokes this method to execute the business logic associated with the process agent.
      void finish()

      void init(IBusinessProcess businessProcess)
      The Unvired infrastructure invokes this method to initialize the process agent.
